CDS90abc | Senior Thesis in Control and Dynamical Systems | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=CDS90abc Senior Thesis in Control and Dynamical Systems | instructors:Murray description:9 units (0-0-9); first, second, third terms Prerequisite: CDS 110, CDS 112 or CDS 140 (may be taken concurrently) Research in control and dynamical systems, supervised by a Caltech faculty member The topic selection is determined by the adviser and the student and is subject to approval by the CDS faculty First and second terms: midterm progress report and oral presentation during finals week Third term: completion of thesis and final presentation Not offered on a pass/fail basis  
CDS101 | Design and Analysis of Feedback Systems | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=CDS101 Design and Analysis of Feedback Systems | instructors:Murray prereq:Ma 1 and Ma 2 or equivalents description:6 units (2-0-4); first term An introduction to feedback and control in physical, biological, engineering, and information sciences Basic principles of feedback and its use as a tool for altering the dynamics of systems and managing uncertainty Key themes throughout the course will include input/output response, modeling and model reduction, linear vs nonlinear models, and local vs global behavior This course is taught concurrently with CDS 110, but is intended for students who are interested primarily in the concepts and tools of control theory and not the analytical techniques for design and synthesis of control systems  
CDS110 | Introduction to Feedback Control Systems | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=CDS110 Introduction to Feedback Control Systems | instructors:Murray prereq:Ma 1abc and Ma 2/102 or equivalents description:12 units (3-0-9); first term An introduction to analysis and design of feedback control systems, including classical control theory in the time and frequency domain Input/output modeling of dynamical systems using differential equations and transfer functions Stability and performance of interconnected systems, including use of block diagrams, Bode plots, the Nyquist criterion, and Lyapunov functions Design of feedback controllers in state space and frequency domain based on stability, performance and robustness specifications  
CDS112 | Control System Design | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=CDS112 Control System Design | instructors:Doyle prereq:CDS 110 description:9 units (3-0-6); second term Optimization-based design of control systems, including optimal control and receding horizon control Robustness and uncertainty management in feedback systems through stochastic and deterministic methods Introductory random processes, Kalman filtering, and norms of signals and systems  
CDS140 | Introduction to Dynamics | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=CDS140 Introduction to Dynamics | instructors:Murray prereq:Ma 2/102 or equivalent, CMS/ACM 104 description:9 units (3-0-6); second term Basics topics in dynamics for continuous state systems in continuous and discrete time, using linear and nonlinear differential equations and maps Topics include equilibria/invariant sets, stability, Lyapunov functions/invariants, attractors and periodic solutions Introduction to structural stability, bifurcations and eigenvalue crossing conditions  
